KATSINA – Governor Aminu Bello Masari of Katsina state has assured the 1,131, 2023 Batch A stream II Corps Members deployed to the state of a safe and condusive environment during their service year. Masari, represented by Ibrahim Khalil Aminu, the Special Adviser Youth Development and Chairman NYSC Governing Board made the pledge on Friday during the Swearing-In Ceremony of the Corps Members in Katsina. He however admonished the Corps Members to shun cultism, drug abuse, religious intolerance and other forms of anti social behaviours. Masari who noted that, the NYSC Corps Members have been very helpful in the development of State, said they have provided the bulk of the required manpower in education and healthcare sectors in the state. He therefore enjoined them, to exhibit discipline by abiding by the rules and regulations of the camp activities to enable them reap the benefits of the one year programme. Hajiya Aisha Muhammad, the state NYSC Coordinator, earlier, disclosed that, a total of 1,131 Corps Members comprising 598 males and 533 females deployed to the state were duly registered for the Orientation Course. Hajia Aisha however informed the Governor of the urgent need for the provision of additional facilities such as Hostel accommodation and Toilets as the existing ones in the camp were grossly inadequate.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ Highlights of the ceremony was the administration of the National Pledge and the NYSC Oath of Allegiance on the Corps Members by the Chief Judge of Katsina State, Justice Musa Danladi Abubakar.